This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with digital image forensics and steganography detection. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves image analysis and detection. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with image manipulation and steganography. The paper also involves machine learning methods, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves the use of Android emulators and reverse engineering techniques.
